edu.umass.cs.gigapaxos.paxosutil

Class PaxosPacketDemultiplexerFast

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.nio.AbstractPacketDemultiplexer<java.lang.Object>
      • edu.umass.cs.gigapaxos.paxosutil.PaxosPacketDemultiplexerFast
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PacketDemultiplexer<java.lang.Object>

    public abstract class PaxosPacketDemultiplexerFast
extends AbstractPacketDemultiplexer<java.lang.Object>
    Author:
    V. Arun

    This is a faster demultiplexer than PaxosPacketDemultiplexerJSON. JSON turns out to be the bottleneck. This class supports json-smart and direct serialization to and from byte[]. The last option is the fastest. We need faster options only for RequestPacket and AcceptPacket; for everything else JSON is just fine. Byteification is a bit harder to maintain, especially the processHeader part, but is worth it for this critical demultiplexer.
